[ProMED-mail does not normally cover outbreaks in endemic regions, but this
outbreak of West Nile virus disease in Israel appears to be more extensive
than usual and it has unusual features. Previously on 8 Sep 2000 the
Jerusalem Post reported that a total of 47 Israelis, all over 60 and many
over 80, had been diagnosed with West Nile fever since the beginning of
August, and there had been 5 fatalities.
According to the Gideon Database, epidemics of West Nile fever were
reported during 1950 to 1954, and in 1957. 61 cases ere reported during
1975 to 1980. In 1998, serum antibody was demonstrated in horses and
migrating white storks (_Ciconia ciconia_). In 1999, 8000 geese were
destroyed when the virus was discovered in commercial flocks. The viral
strain found in these geese was virtually identical to that responsible for
an outbreak in New York City during 1999. The principal vectors are _Culex
univattatus_, _Cx. pipiens_, _C. perexiguus_ and _Anopheles coustani_. -
